    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "Runtime boundary in `goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go` exposes raw transport action input via `ProcessC2CMessage` → `service.Execute(cmd.Action, ...)` without validation through the protocol action contract layer (`ParseC2CAction`).",
        "C2C dispatch wiring is initialized in package scope as `c2cActionDispatcher`, coupling command-routing policy to package lifecycle rather than contract construction at seam boundaries.",
        "The C2C service constructor injects callbacks (`NewC2CServiceForAdapter`) but does not enforce them as required seam dependencies, enabling runtime panic on first call path instead of deterministic contract failure."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "high",
      "sub_axes": {
        "abstraction_leverage": 84.0,
        "indirection_cost": 76.0,
        "interface_honesty": 78.0
      }
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "c2c_unvalidated_action_entry",
      "summary": "C2C command entrypoint accepts unvalidated actions, weakening protocol contracts across module seams.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ProcessC2CMessage` receives `C2CCommand` and forwards `cmd.Action` directly to `service.Execute` without calling `actions.ParseC2CAction`.",
        "`ParseAction` and namespace-specific validators exist in `goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go`, but this boundary is bypassed at the wifi service seam."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Validate `cmd.Action` at the service boundary with `actions.ParseC2CAction` (or a dedicated protocol-to-seam adapter) before executing, and return a typed unsupported-action error for anything outside `NamespaceC2C`.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_contract_seal"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "c2c_dispatcher_global_binding",
      "summary": "Package-scope action dispatcher creates hard module coupling and hides runtime-architecture boundaries.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`var c2cActionDispatcher = actions.NewActionDispatcher(...)` is declared as global state at package scope.",
        "Execution behavior for `ConnectAction` is bound there with inline closure logic, rather than being composed in a seam-aware constructor."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Move dispatcher construction into `NewC2CServiceForAdapter`/`ProcessC2CMessage` and inject it as a dependency so protocol action wiring is explicit per runtime instance and test seam.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_contract_seal"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "c2c_adapter_nil_callbacks",
      "summary": "Adapter contract allows nil seam functions, making the execution seam fail by panic instead of contract error.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go",
        "README.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`NewC2CServiceForAdapter` accepts `connectToWiFi` and `restartGroundSeg` without nil checks.",
        "`C2CServiceExecutor.ConnectToWiFi` and `RestartGroundSeg` invoke function fields unconditionally.",
        "The root README frames these as explicit seam contracts and expects stable runtime boundaries, but constructor currently accepts incomplete adapters silently."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make the constructor (or a `Validate` path) enforce non-nil adapters and return an explicit error, or provide no-op guarded behavior with clear diagnostics before service registration.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_contract_seal"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Runtime contracts at the C2C seam are under-enforced: action validation and seam dependency integrity are not centralized into a deterministic contract boundary.",
      "Protocol-to-service coupling is direct and global, reducing modular governance around transport-action ownership."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "c2c_unvalidated_action_entry",
      "c2c_dispatcher_global_binding",
      "c2c_adapter_nil_callbacks"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "If all `C2CCommand` callers are already validated upstream and never reach this boundary with malformed callbacks/actions, the first two findings may overstate operational risk."
    ]
  }
}


